org.synchronoss.cpo

Interface CpoReleasible

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CassandraBoundStatementFactory, CpoStatementFactory, JdbcCallableStatementFactory, JdbcPreparedStatementFactory, OracleTemporaryBlob, OracleTemporaryClob

    public interface CpoReleasible
    CpoReleasible is a class that can be called during a CpoTransform when there are resources that need to released after the current prepared statement is processed. examples are in the the TransformBlob where there are Oracle resources that must exist until the statement is executed.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void release()
      release is called by the CPO framework.

    • Method Detail

      • release

        void release()
      throws CpoException
        release is called by the CPO framework. A transform can register a CpoReleasible that will be called when the current prepared or callable statement has been executed.
        Throws:
        CpoException
